{
  "answer": "**I could not locate any Ghalib couplet in the Falsafa corpus matching or closely paraphrasing \"why should I not weep — the world has forgotten me too?\"**\n\nThe corpus contains *Diwan-E-Ghalib* (239 chapters/ghazals).[^1] Extensive searches across English translations for key phrases (\"why should I not weep\", \"world has forgotten me\", \"forgotten me too\", \"weep forgotten\", combinations like \"why\" + \"weep\" + \"world\", etc.) yielded no results. Broader searches for \"weep\" and \"forgotten\" surfaced thematic near-misses:\n\n- Ghazal 190: \"I would not weep for solace, if the joy of sight were near\" and \"Why should the world, through me, find out that you live here?\"[^2]\n- Ghazal 73: \"Should you have forgotten me, let me remind you of my place\" (with delay/ruin themes).[^3]\n- Ghazal 102: \"To be forgotten is the cross I gain is mine\" (with weeping friends).[^4]\n\nThese evoke abandonment/weeping but do not match. The phrasing may reflect a different translation, variant, or unattributed paraphrase not present here.\n\n[^1]: *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, work overview, [work wiki](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/wiki/_work.card.md).\n\n[^2]: *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 190, [p-45286c](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/190-taskeen-ko-hum-na-royein-jo-zauq-e-nazar-mile/translation/#p-45286c) and [p-36f420](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/190-taskeen-ko-hum-na-royein-jo-zauq-e-nazar-mile/translation/#p-36f420).\n\n[^3]: *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 73, [p-85cc4e](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/73-hui-taakhir-to-kuch-baais-e-taakhir-bhi-tha/translation/#p-85cc4e).\n\n[^4]: *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 102, [p-8d8ade](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/102-kab-woh-sunta-hai-kahani-meri/translation/#p-8d8ade).",
